  "prompt": "How many layers should you wear on cold winter days?",
  "response": "The number of layers you should wear on cold winter days depends on various factors like the temperature, wind chill, your activity level, and your personal tolerance to cold. Generally, a three-layer system is recommended:\n\n1. **Base Layer:** This layer should be moisture-wicking to keep sweat away from your skin. Materials like wool, polyester, or other synthetics work well.\n2. **Mid Layer:** This layer provides insulation to retain body heat. Fleece, down, or synthetic insulated jackets are common choices.\n3. **Outer Layer:** The outer layer should be windproof and waterproof to protect against the elements. Look for a good quality shell jacket made from Gore-Tex or similar materials.\n\nYou can adjust these layers based on the conditions and your comfort. Additionally, don't forget accessories like hats, scarves, gloves, and warm socks to protect extremities.",
